	"entries": [
		"You attempt to plunge the mind of a creature you can see within range into an illusory reality. The target makes an Intelligence saving throw. On a failed save, you create a phantasmal environment that is no larger than a 60-foot-radius {@variantrule Sphere [Area of Effect]|XPHB|Sphere} centered on the target. The environment can include creatures, objects, or other phenomenon but is only perceivable to the target. The phantasm includes sound, temperature, and other stimuli. The area outside the phantasm is {@variantrule Heavily Obscured|XPHB} by black mist.",
		"The target can take a {@action Study|XPHB} action to examine the phantasm with an Intelligence ({@skill Investigation|XPHB}) check against your spell save DC. If the check succeeds, the target realizes that the phantasm is an illusion, and the spell ends.",
		"While affected by the spell, the target treats the phantasm as if it were real and rationalizes any illogical outcomes from interacting with it. For example, if the target steps through a phantasmal bridge and survives the fall, it believes the bridge exists and something else caused it to fall. Additionally, other non-illusory creatures cannot be perceived by the target and are considered {@condition Invisible|XPHB}. Interactions with other creatures are rationalized in the same manner as interactions with the phantasm.",
		"An affected target can even take damage from the illusion if the phantasm holds dangerous creatures or hazards. On each of your turns, such a phantasm can deal {@damage 2d8} Psychic damage to the target. The target perceives the damage as a type appropriate to the illusion."
